          "tz": 180
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Vladimir Saveliev",
          "email": "c17830@cray.com",
          "date": "2018-05-29 11:47:35.000000000",
          "tz": 180
        },
        "subject": "LU-11053 llite: check loop device file size before read",
        "message": "LU-11053 llite: check loop device file size before read\n\nll_file_open() does not fill lustre's inode->i_size. That makes a\nproblem for losetup which avoid stat(). loop block device file gets\nzero file size from lustre's inode, that ends with failure on\numounting the loop device at BUG_ON(!buffer_mapped(bh)) in\nsubmit_bh().\n\nThe proposed fix is to check loop device file size during reading loop\ndevice and to refuse to read if it mismatches lustre file size.\n\nsanity.sh:test_54c() is modified to illistrate how mounting loop\ndevice file fails without having lustre backing file stat-ed before\nlosetup and how it succeeds when stat precedes losetup.\n\nSigned-off-by: Vladimir Saveliev <c17830@cray.com>\nChange-Id: I75e211d6b417134420281a67d87c5e75485f8727\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
  "requirements": [],
  "submit_records": []
